name: Manufacturing New Export Orders Index

name: Manufacturing Inventories Index
description: As of January 2012, the Inventories Index is no longer seasonally adjusted.

name: PMI Composite Index
description: The PMI (R) is a composite index based on the diffusion indexes of five of the indexes with equal weights: New Orders (seasonally adjusted), Production (seasonally adjusted), Employment (seasonally adjusted), Supplier Deliveries (seasonally adjusted), and Inventories.

name: Manufacturing Prices Index
description: As of January 2003, the Prices Index is no longer seasonally adjusted.

Services PMI New Export Orders Index
Services PMI Imports Index
description: Formerly Non-Manufacturing. As of January 2003, Imports will no longer be seasonally adjusted.

name: Services PMI Index (Formerly Non-Manufacturing)
description: The Services PMI (R) (Formerly Non-Manufacturing) is a composite index based on the diffusion indexes for four of the indicators with equal weights: Business Activity (seasonally adjusted), New Orders (seasonally adjusted), Employment (seasonally adjusted) and Supplier Deliveries. Diffusion indexes have the properties of leading indicators and are convenient summary measures showing the prevailing direction of change and the scope of change.
